      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NOT SORRY (1) stalked the lead from a low draw and fought on well to finish half a length back in second (22.96) at Geelong in a Rank Limit - Grade 5 over 400m. Ready to find winning form. NOCTILUCENT (7) is a talented type and proved too strong last time to win by 1.3 lengths at Ballarat in a handy 22.06 beating Tension Head. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and four minor placings to her credit. One of the leading chances again. CINNABAR ICON (3) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing sixth (22.58) last time in a Grade 4/5 at this track. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings four times from seven attempts. Can measure up this time. Something for the Multiples: RIPPER RILEY (2)",
